      "description": "Available is a mechanically sorted 2008 BMW M3 (E92) featuring the high-revving S65 4.0L V8. This naturally aspirated power plant utilizes individual throttle bodies and double-VANOS to achieve an 8,400 RPM redline. Power is sent to the rear wheels via a 6-speed manual gearbox and an M Variable Differential Lock, ensuring exceptional mechanical grip. The chassis maintains its structural integrity, featuring a carbon fiber reinforced plastic (CFRP) roof to lower the center of gravity and aluminum multi-link suspension for reduced unsprung mass. Recent preventative maintenance includes rod bearing inspection and throttle actuator service. While the aesthetics show honest patina consistent with its age, the drivetrain remains tight and the hydraulic steering rack offers the tactile feedback desired by purists. A formidable driver's car with a visceral exhaust note.",
